  "text": "The shape of at least 200 pellets from each formulation was characterized using the methodology reported earlier [CITATION_1] . The images of pellets captured using an image analyzer connected to a digital camera (DSP 3CCD, Sony, Tokyo, Fig. 1 . SEM photomicrographs of the dry MCC particles; a PH102, b PH101, and c PH105 Japan) mounted on a stereomicroscope (SZH, Olympus, Tokyo, Japan) were analyzed (Image-Pro, Version 6.3, Media Cybernetics, Bethesda, MD, USA) for circularity. Circularity describes the sphericity of pellets. The circularity value of a perfectly round pellet is 1.",
